Response ID: resp_518
Response Text: I would love to see ACME work with the Austin Community Foundation to develop a Fund that could expand funding opportunities for the arts which we know there's a severe lack of outside of current city funding. This could be a natural place to direct private foundations and donors as well. Austin has long been lacking in major arts funders outside of the HOT funds and Moody Foundation investments into venues. 

Review of insurance requirements for artists to be contractors or participate in city programs. E.g. the Parks dept had outdated contractor requirements for insurance that are cost prohibitive to one-time performers/instructors for a recent Day of Dance event at AARC. Even though the coverage minimums were low, the addition of Waivers of Subrogration and lack of insurers will to provide that low of minimums coverage had the cost of insurance exceeding the amount the vendor would be paid by the City.

